    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are acting weird. the leaves on the bottom are turning all yellow and kind of pale. any idea what happened or how to fix it?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Yellowing lower leaves on tomato plants, a classic sign of trouble, is often a tell-tale sign of a nutrient deficiency, like nitrogen, or sometimes overwatering. You can try gently checking the soil moisture; if it's constantly soggy, that's probably the culprit, and you need to let it dry out a bit. If the soil is dry but the leaves are yellowing, a balanced fertilizer might be what your thirsty plants are craving.",
